  "body": "BIP324 mentions K1 is used for the associated data and K2 is used for the payload. The code does the opposite. This is not a security problem but will be a problem across implementations based on the HKDF key derivations.\r\n\r\nBIP324 author Jonas Schnelli thinks a [code update will be better](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/15649#discussion_r440780669) than a BIP update.\r\n\r\nIf this PR is merged:\r\n\r\n- [ ] We need to update the test vector 3 in BIP324",
